(c) 
\f2\i Dollar thresholds
\f0\i0 . Unless otherwise specified, a specific dollar threshold for the purpose of applicability is the final anticipated dollar value of the action, including the dollar value of all options. If the action establishes a maximum quantity of supplies or services to be acquired or establishes a ceiling price or establishes the final price to be based on future events, the final anticipated dollar value must be the highest final priced alternative to the Government, including the dollar value of all options.\
(d) 
\f2\i Application of FAR changes to solicitations and contracts
\f0\i0 . Unless otherwise specified-\
(1) FAR changes apply to solicitations issued on or after the effective date of the change;\
(2) Contracting officers may, at their discretion, include the FAR changes in solicitations issued before the effective\
date, provided award of the resulting contract(s) occurs on or after the effective date; and\
(3) Contracting officers may, at their discretion, include the changes in any existing contract with appropriate\
consideration.\
(e) 
\f2\i Citations
\f0\i0 . When the FAR cites a statute, Executive order, Office of Management and Budget circular, Office of Federal\
Procurement Policy policy letter, or relevant portion of the 
\f2\i Code of Federal Regulations
\f0\i0 , the citation includes all applicable amendments, unless otherwise stated.\
(f) 
\f2\i Imperative sentences
\f0\i0 . When an imperative sentence directs action, the contracting officer is responsible for the action, unless another party is expressly cited.\
